"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-simone-biles-conquers-the-vault-third-gold-medal-of-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 Even Simone Biles sometimes gets caught up in the legend of Simone Biles.\\u00c2  As she stood atop the podium during Saturday\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s vault final, preparing to unleash the flips that would earn her her third gold medal of these Olympics and her 10th overall, her coach Laurent Landi signaled to her:Wait.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 270, \"end\": 283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurent_Landi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laurent Landi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurent_Landi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurent_Landi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cObviously once you get up there, your adrenaline is pumping,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she said afterward.\", \"from\": 307, \"to\": 393, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cHe wanted to make sure that I was staying calm and going on my own time, even though the thing said GO and everybody started cheering.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  As she has all Olympics, Biles blocked out the expectations of others and focused on her own.\", \"from\": 394, \"to\": 629, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 497, \"end\": 499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GO_Transit\", \"score\": 0.999935952692091, \"rank\": 6.404792038565845e-05, \"text\": \"GO\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GO_Transit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GO_Transit\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She took a breath and began sprinting down the runway.\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 684, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When she landed the Yurchenko double pike vault that bears her name\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094the Biles II, one of five eponymous skills\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094it was all but over.\\u00c2  She sealed gold with a less complicated vault that made her combined score a preposterous 15.300.\", \"from\": 685, \"to\": 920, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 705, \"end\": 714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yurchenko_(vault)\", \"score\": 0.9924615128803714, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yurchenko\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yurchenko_(vault)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yurchenko_(vault)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brazil\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Rebeca Andrade, the best gymnast on earth not named Biles, and the 2023 world champion in the vault, finished second with a score of 14.966.\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 1072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 932, \"end\": 946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rebeca Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jade Carey, who has spent the past three years reliving the instant when she stumbled on the runway in Tokyo and finished last in this event, took bronze.\\u00c2  Biles hadlamented Andrade\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s skillsafter Thursday\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s individual all-around final, saying, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t want to compete with Rebeca no more!\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1073, \"end\": 1083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Carey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jade Carey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Carey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Carey\"}, {\"begin\": 1176, \"end\": 1181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999990714059, \"rank\": 9.241760567080606e-10, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m tired!\", \"from\": 1372, \"to\": 1384, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s way too close.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d On Saturday, after Andrade\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s first vault, Biles turned to Carey, grinned and shrugged dramatically, as if to say, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWhat are we supposed to do about her?\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  But Biles, 27, had already done what she needed to do, and everyone in Bercy Arena knew it.\", \"from\": 1385, \"to\": 1663, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1471, \"end\": 1476, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.444411560226187e-17, \"text\": \"Carey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\"}, {\"begin\": 1643, \"end\": 1654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bercy Arena\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her difficulty score is so high that as long as she stays on her feet, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s almost impossible for anyone else to match her.\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1789, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Andrade actually executed her vaults better, by more than two-tenths of a point, but it didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t matter.\\u00c2  This was Biles\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s fourth Yurchenko double pike in competition this week\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094once in the qualifiers,once in the team final,once in the individual all-around\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and she said she would be retiring the skill.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI mean, I kind of nailed that one,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she said with a grin.\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 2164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1790, \"end\": 1797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8574740460528046e-16, \"text\": \"Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\"}, {\"begin\": 1923, \"end\": 1932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yurchenko_(vault)\", \"score\": 0.9924615128803714, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yurchenko\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yurchenko_(vault)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yurchenko_(vault)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As for herself, she was less decisive.\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2204, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cNever say never,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she said.\", \"from\": 2205, \"to\": 2237, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe next Olympics is at home, so you never know.\", \"from\": 2238, \"to\": 2289, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I am getting really old.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  As she has all week, Biles set records in both age and decoration: She became the oldest woman to win gold in the vault since Ekaterina Kalinchuk, representing the Soviet Union, did so at 30 in 1952, the first time women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s gymnastics were contested at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2290, \"to\": 2590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2449, \"end\": 2468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ekaterina_Kalinchuk\", \"score\": 0.9999998259695682, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ekaterina Kalinchuk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ekaterina_Kalinchuk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ekaterina_Kalinchuk\"}, {\"begin\": 2494, \"end\": 2499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999998167368, \"rank\": 1.830826752054851e-10, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And Biles\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s gold today, her second on vault after she also won in Rio, tied her with runner Allyson Felix for second most golds by a U.S. woman.\", \"from\": 2591, \"to\": 2737, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2659, \"end\": 2662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999998085514, \"rank\": 1.9155463667647907e-10, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2685, \"end\": 2698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allyson_Felix\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Allyson Felix\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allyson_Felix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allyson_Felix\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Swimmers Jenny Thompson and Katie Ledecky each have eight.)\", \"from\": 2738, \"to\": 2798, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2748, \"end\": 2762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Thompson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jenny Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 2767, \"end\": 2780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles also now owns 40 Olympic and world championship medals, 30 of them gold.\\u00c2  Although Saturday\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s vaults were smooth, the process of getting there was not.\", \"from\": 2799, \"to\": 2959, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Tokyo, it was on the vault, of course, that the twisties that had dogged her for weeks became insurmountable.\", \"from\": 2960, \"to\": 3072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2963, \"end\": 2968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999990714059, \"rank\": 9.241760567080606e-10, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She fell out of her vault\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094an Amanar, which entails two and a half twists\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094during the team final and withdrew from event after event before stripping the twisting elements from her balance beam routine and gutting out a bronze medal.\", \"from\": 3073, \"to\": 3308, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3104, \"end\": 3110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amanar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.410891475811783e-75, \"text\": \"Amanar\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amanar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amanar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She took a year off from practicing and two off from competition before returning in 2023, and she initially performed the Amanar again, but she scrapped it in favor of the Biles II, which has two flips but no twists.\\u00c2  That was at Landi\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s request, he said afterward, pointing out that even a one-point deduction for a fall on the Biles II would bring her score down only to the start value for the Amanar.\", \"from\": 3309, \"to\": 3717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3432, \"end\": 3438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amanar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.410891475811783e-75, \"text\": \"Amanar\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amanar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amanar\"}, {\"begin\": 3710, \"end\": 3716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amanar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.410891475811783e-75, \"text\": \"Amanar\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amanar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amanar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So what the hell?\\\"\", \"from\": 3718, \"to\": 3737, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"he said.\", \"from\": 3738, \"to\": 3746, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI think we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re both still a little bit traumatized [from] Tokyo,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Biles said.\", \"from\": 3748, \"to\": 3831, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3810, \"end\": 3815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999990714059, \"rank\": 9.241760567080606e-10, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAnd we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re excited that I can do multiple vaults, so that we don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t have to use the two and a half.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Otherwise, she said, her mental health is in good shape as she heads into her final two events here, Monday\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s beam final and floor exercise final.\", \"from\": 3832, \"to\": 4089, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She has been speaking frequently with her therapist, despite the time difference, but she felt that she did not need the extra support on Saturday morning.\", \"from\": 4090, \"to\": 4245, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She has insisted that after so many years of worrying about what other people thought, she is focused only on herself.\", \"from\": 4246, \"to\": 4364, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She did, however, make time to comment on all the people who questioned her in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 4365, \"to\": 4450, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4444, \"end\": 4449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999990714059, \"rank\": 9.241760567080606e-10, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThey\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re really quiet right now,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she noted.\\u00c2  Her fans are not.\", \"from\": 4451, \"to\": 4521, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But gymnastics, Landi said, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cis in the head, more than the physical aspect.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d And all week, Biles has been able to ignore the noise  Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 4522, \"to\": 4684, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Stephanie Apstein is a senior writer covering baseball and Olympic sports for Sports Illustrated, where she started as an intern in 2011 and has since covered a dozen World Series and three Olympics.\", \"from\": 4685, \"to\": 4948, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4749, \"end\": 4758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_McMahon\", \"score\": 0.9999261543235363, \"rank\": 7.379212835301462e-05, \"text\": \"Stephanie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_McMahon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_McMahon\"}, {\"begin\": 4827, \"end\": 4845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8977303190106904e-20, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has twice won top honors from the Associated Press Sports Editors, and her work has been included in the Best American Sports Writing book series.\", \"from\": 4949, \"to\": 5099, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4987, \"end\": 5003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999999999704414, \"rank\": 2.928390018444114e-11, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 5058, \"end\": 5086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Best_American_Sports_Writing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Best American Sports Writing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Best_American_Sports_Writing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Best_American_Sports_Writing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She graduated from Trinity College with a bachelor\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s in French and Italian, and has a master\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s in journalism from Columbia University.\", \"from\": 5100, \"to\": 5238, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5119, \"end\": 5134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duke_University\", \"score\": 0.9975521797736017, \"rank\": 0.002453826752577278, \"text\": \"Trinity College\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duke_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duke_University\"}, {\"begin\": 5218, \"end\": 5237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Columbia_University\", \"score\": 0.9999992800610789, \"rank\": 7.137221200748219e-07, \"text\": \"Columbia University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Columbia_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Columbia_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC.\", \"from\": 5240, \"to\": 5317, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"- All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 5318, \"to\": 53